videoSnippet.title: Oh Capablanca! | Ivanchuk vs Adhiban || Capablanca Memorial (2019)
videoSnippet.description:
Follow me on Instagram for extra content https://www.instagram.com/agadmator/

Capablanca Memorial (2019), Havana CUB, rd 10, May-14 
Modern Defense (B06)

1. d4 d6 2. e4 g6 3. c4 Bg7 4. Nc3 c5 5. Nge2 Nc6 6. d5 Na5 7. Rb1 Nf6 8. Ng3 O-O 9. Be2 e6 10. O-O exd5 11. cxd5 a6 12. b4 Nd7 13. Qd2 cxb4 14. Nd1 h5 15. Bxh5 Nc4 16. Qxb4 b5 17. Be2 Nc5 18. Bxc4 bxc4 19. Bb2 Nd3 20. Qa3 Nxb2 21. Nxb2 c3 22. Nc4 Qc7 23. Na5 Rb8 24. Rxb8 Qxb8 25. Nc6 Qb5 26. Qxd6 c2 27. Qc7 Bf6 28. Na7 Qb7 29. Qxb7 Bxb7 30. Rc1 Bg5 31. Rxc2 f5 32. Rc7 Ba8 33. Nc6 Bf4 34. Ra7 Bxc6 35. dxc6 Re8 36. Rxa6 fxe4 37. Ra4

The 54th edition of the Capablanca Memorial is taking place from May 3-13 in the Habana Libre Hotel in Havana, Cuba. The elite group of the event honouring the Cuban Chess World Champion José Raúl Capablanca is a double round-robin with Baskaran Adhiban as top seed.

Players receive 90 minutes for 40 moves, followed by 30 minutes to the end of the game, with a 30-second increment starting from move one. Official website: torneocapablanca.inder.cu
